00:06:46.140 --> 00:06:48.782
Next is interestingly
something that we've

00:06:48.782 --> 00:06:50.240
learned over the
past few years, is

00:06:50.240 --> 00:06:53.440
that as you go out there and
try to build a global payments

00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:56.090
platform, you actually
have to think very locally.

00:06:56.090 --> 00:06:58.880
There is no silver bullet.

00:06:58.880 --> 00:07:01.310
There's no payment method
that works everywhere.

00:07:01.310 --> 00:07:04.100
There's no easy way to do this.

00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:05.740
You just have to go
into each market.

00:07:05.740 --> 00:07:07.240
You have to understand
that market--

00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:09.640
the behavior, the
purchase experience, what

00:07:09.640 --> 00:07:11.450
people are most familiar with.

00:07:11.450 --> 00:07:14.620
And then you have to build
a product that works there.

00:07:14.620 --> 00:07:16.440
And so in the US,
as you'd imagine,

00:07:16.440 --> 00:07:18.240
credit cards are very popular.

00:07:18.240 --> 00:07:21.120
That is the primary way
that people want to buy.

00:07:21.120 --> 00:07:25.630
In Japan, carrier billing
is extremely popular.

00:07:25.630 --> 00:07:29.100
And so these are two incredibly
important markets for us

00:07:29.100 --> 00:07:31.220
that behave in
completely different ways

00:07:31.220 --> 00:07:32.990
when it comes to payments.

00:07:32.990 --> 00:07:36.040
And so again, we had
to go in and start

00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:37.460
thinking very locally.

00:07:37.460 --> 00:07:40.290
And this replicates to
every other market almost.

00:07:40.290 --> 00:07:42.510
Every other country,
actually, is this way.

00:07:42.510 --> 00:07:46.082
There's a distinction
in behavior.

00:07:46.082 --> 00:07:46.790
So what do we do?

00:07:46.790 --> 00:07:50.140
So one of things we've done
over the past couple of years--

00:07:50.140 --> 00:07:52.280
so two years ago, we launched
Google Play gift card

00:07:52.280 --> 00:07:54.050
in the US only.

00:07:54.050 --> 00:07:56.340
Today, it is in 18 markets.

00:07:56.340 --> 00:07:58.670
And I think as of
maybe this morning,

00:07:58.670 --> 00:08:00.340
it's in its 19th market.

00:08:00.340 --> 00:08:02.480
So we've been very
aggressively rolling

00:08:02.480 --> 00:08:03.870
out the Google Play gift card.

00:08:03.870 --> 00:08:06.090
It's been very successful
for us, because one,

00:08:06.090 --> 00:08:09.590
it unlocks new segment of users
that just don't-- they just

00:08:09.590 --> 00:08:12.310
don't have access to credit
cards or other kinds of more

00:08:12.310 --> 00:08:14.120
fluid forms of payment.

00:08:14.120 --> 00:08:16.600
And two, it gets
the brand out there,

00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:19.150
and it gets users-- this
is in the physical world.

00:08:19.150 --> 00:08:20.630
This is in retailers.

00:08:20.630 --> 00:08:23.500
This is in tens of
thousands of locations

00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:25.540
that we now have the
Google Play brand known.

00:08:25.540 --> 00:08:29.800
And your users, while they
are in their usual day-to-day

00:08:29.800 --> 00:08:32.260
habits, they're seeing
the Google Play gift card.

00:08:32.260 --> 00:08:34.230
The other one is
direct carrier billing,

00:08:34.230 --> 00:08:36.190
which has been very
successful for us.

00:08:36.190 --> 00:08:40.299
And it is now in 25 markets,
as Michael [INAUDIBLE] earlier.

00:08:40.299 --> 00:08:43.662
And finally, PayPal, which
we launched more recently--

00:08:43.662 --> 00:08:45.370
it's been very successful
for us as well.

00:08:45.370 --> 00:08:50.030
It's now in 12 markets and
rolling out to more shortly.

00:08:50.030 --> 00:08:52.670
So again, these
are current stats.

00:08:52.670 --> 00:08:54.210
They're changing constantly.

00:08:54.210 --> 00:08:56.190
But the objective
is as a user comes

00:08:56.190 --> 00:08:59.320
in from any of your
countries, any users

00:08:59.320 --> 00:09:01.924
that you have in any
markets, as they come in,

00:09:01.924 --> 00:09:03.340
the objective is
that they'll find

00:09:03.340 --> 00:09:05.700
an option on their
purchase experience

00:09:05.700 --> 00:09:08.160
that is familiar to them
that they want to use.

00:09:08.160 --> 00:09:09.760
We want to reduce that hurdle.

00:09:09.760 --> 00:09:13.390
So this is a major
part of what I do

00:09:13.390 --> 00:09:16.630
and what the entire team
at Google Play does.

00:09:16.630 --> 00:09:18.490
And I'll give you a
bit of a case study

00:09:18.490 --> 00:09:21.732
about the launch of the Google
Play gift card in Germany.

00:09:21.732 --> 00:09:23.190
And this will give
you some insight

00:09:23.190 --> 00:09:25.175
about our overall
strategy for payments.

00:09:28.800 --> 00:09:32.970
OK, so as we launched the
Google Play gift card,

00:09:32.970 --> 00:09:38.409
over the past year, we had
70% increase in buyers.

00:09:38.409 --> 00:09:39.200
This is tremendous.

00:09:39.200 --> 00:09:40.820
This is like step
change type stuff.

00:09:40.820 --> 00:09:43.320
And if you look at-- a lot of
you are potentially developers

00:09:43.320 --> 00:09:46.730
already selling in Germany, you
would have seen that impact.

00:09:46.730 --> 00:09:48.860
And so the launch
of a form of payment

00:09:48.860 --> 00:09:50.660
that is convenient
to a market, that

00:09:50.660 --> 00:09:52.230
is familiar to
users in a market,

00:09:52.230 --> 00:09:54.340
has a significant impact.

00:09:54.340 --> 00:09:56.630
So the interesting
thing is what did this

00:09:56.630 --> 00:09:59.589
do to the rest of the
purchase flow conversion rate?

00:09:59.589 --> 00:10:01.880
Actualy, it increased our
purchase flow conversion rate

00:10:01.880 --> 00:10:02.379
by 25%.

00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:08.330
So more of those clicks that
are coming from your apps

00:10:08.330 --> 00:10:11.700
are converted-- to
be clear, 25% more.

00:10:11.700 --> 00:10:13.500
And that's huge.

00:10:13.500 --> 00:10:17.230
That is incredibly significant
for all of you who are actually

00:10:17.230 --> 00:10:20.380
closing more of those sales
and completing those sales.

00:10:20.380 --> 00:10:22.330
And finally, what
this does overall--

00:10:22.330 --> 00:10:24.350
because at the
end of the day, we

00:10:24.350 --> 00:10:26.420
care about overall
sales in the country.

00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:31.880
And that actually had
a 3x impact on sales.

00:10:31.880 --> 00:10:37.510
So over the last year, sales
in Germany have grown by 3x.

00:10:37.510 --> 00:10:40.640
And while this is tied to a
number of things-- including

00:10:40.640 --> 00:10:42.920
growth in Android,
including the availability

00:10:42.920 --> 00:10:45.300
of preferred methods, and the
increase in the conversion

00:10:45.300 --> 00:10:47.160
rate-- this is a
trend that we want

00:10:47.160 --> 00:10:49.500
to see more and more markets in.

00:10:49.500 --> 00:10:53.780
We activate the buyers, we
launch good forms of payment,

00:10:53.780 --> 00:10:55.921
and then we see an increase
in revenue like this.

00:10:55.921 --> 00:10:57.420
This is a success
story that we want

00:10:57.420 --> 00:11:00.780
to replicate in many,
many more countries.

00:11:00.780 --> 00:11:04.390
For example, we launched
carrier billing and gift cards

00:11:04.390 --> 00:11:05.740
in Hong Kong.

00:11:05.740 --> 00:11:10.040
And in that country, we had
an 80% growth in buyers.

00:11:10.040 --> 00:11:11.960
In Russia, we launched
carrier billing,

00:11:11.960 --> 00:11:15.750
and we had 100% growth
in number of buyers.

00:11:15.750 --> 00:11:17.880
So again, we're
hoping that this will

00:11:17.880 --> 00:11:19.790
be replicated in every market.

00:11:19.790 --> 00:11:24.160
And we're working very hard
to make sure that we do.

00:11:24.160 --> 00:11:27.084
Shifting a bit to the
purchase experience

00:11:27.084 --> 00:11:29.500
is not only about the forms
of payment available, but also

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:31.110
where they are available.

00:11:31.110 --> 00:11:34.110
And this was-- I always
thought of this as a gap

00:11:34.110 --> 00:11:37.560
where on tablets, carrier
billing was not available.

00:11:37.560 --> 00:11:39.960
And just maybe I'll step
back and say carrier billing

00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:42.620
is when you're able to
buy something and put it

00:11:42.620 --> 00:11:46.030
on your operator bill,
your monthly operator bill.

00:11:46.030 --> 00:11:48.710
And it was not
available in tablets

00:11:48.710 --> 00:11:51.044
because you could imagine
the setup experience requires

00:11:51.044 --> 00:11:52.460
you to be on the
phone that you're

00:11:52.460 --> 00:11:53.850
going to bill the stuff to.

00:11:53.850 --> 00:11:56.147
But we've built new technology
over the past couple

00:11:56.147 --> 00:11:57.980
of years that allowed
us to actually now run

00:11:57.980 --> 00:12:00.170
carrier billing
from Wi-Fi tablets.

00:12:00.170 --> 00:12:03.910
And so if you're a user that
primarily uses carrier billing,

00:12:03.910 --> 00:12:06.707
and you're on your phone, when
you went to the tablet before,

00:12:06.707 --> 00:12:08.290
you actually couldn't
make a purchase.

00:12:08.290 --> 00:12:10.500
You didn't have an
available form of payment.

00:12:10.500 --> 00:12:12.770
Today they can, and that's
had a significant impact

00:12:12.770 --> 00:12:15.759
on monetization on
that device segment.

00:12:15.759 --> 00:12:17.050
So that's been really exciting.

00:12:19.750 --> 00:12:21.410
Another thing that
we have learned

00:12:21.410 --> 00:12:25.670
is that locally developed
content is extremely important.

00:12:25.670 --> 00:12:28.400
It kind of triggers
the entire ecosystem.

00:12:28.400 --> 00:12:30.790
And we've worked really
hard over the past year

00:12:30.790 --> 00:12:33.670
to enable developers in
more and more countries

00:12:33.670 --> 00:12:36.182
to be able to sell
on Google Play.

00:12:36.182 --> 00:12:38.640
And this may not impact all of
you, because if you're here,

00:12:38.640 --> 00:12:41.450
you're probably already
a successful developer.

00:12:41.450 --> 00:12:44.300
Maybe a dozen-- I've talked
to someone from Bulgaria.

00:12:44.300 --> 00:12:46.690
But essentially, we've
launched 22 new markets.

00:12:46.690 --> 00:12:48.559
We're at 54 markets today.

00:12:48.559 --> 00:12:50.100
And our objective--
this is something

00:12:50.100 --> 00:12:53.900
that we really care about
at the mission level.

00:12:53.900 --> 00:12:56.460
We want to make sure
that anyone that

00:12:56.460 --> 00:12:58.350
can build an awesome
Android application,

00:12:58.350 --> 00:13:00.490
no matter where they are,
they can earn a living

00:13:00.490 --> 00:13:01.800
on Google Play.

00:13:01.800 --> 00:13:03.170
It's that simple.

00:13:03.170 --> 00:13:04.780
Anyone anywhere
should be able to earn

00:13:04.780 --> 00:13:07.330
a living on Google Play.

00:13:07.330 --> 00:13:09.085
And so we're at 54 countries.

00:13:09.085 --> 00:13:10.460
We're going to
continue to launch

00:13:10.460 --> 00:13:15.290
more and more of these markets
over the next few months.

00:13:15.290 --> 00:13:18.350
All right, so what can
you do to make sure

00:13:18.350 --> 00:13:20.800
that you're taking advantage
of this global platform?

00:13:20.800 --> 00:13:25.040
This is hopefully the
actionable part for you.

00:13:25.040 --> 00:13:28.150
First of all is
localizing your listings.

00:13:28.150 --> 00:13:30.020
This is incredibly important.

00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:33.260
Now, of course, you can't
localize to every language.

00:13:33.260 --> 00:13:35.580
But if you are intentionally
selling in a market,

00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:37.620
if you're intentionally
acquiring users

00:13:37.620 --> 00:13:39.910
through ads in a
market, if you want

00:13:39.910 --> 00:13:41.590
to grow your
business in a market,

00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:44.210
you have to actually speak
that country's language.

00:13:44.210 --> 00:13:47.030
It is an absolute,
just basic thing

00:13:47.030 --> 00:13:50.500
that many developers don't
actually do, unfortunately.

00:13:50.500 --> 00:13:53.090
And the Developer Console
offers all sorts of tools

00:13:53.090 --> 00:13:55.960
to make this really
accessible for developers.

00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:58.296
So whether you're using
professional translation tools

00:13:58.296 --> 00:14:00.670
or you're actually using the
Developer Console one, which

00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:03.680
gets routed to professionals,
that is really important.

00:14:03.680 --> 00:14:06.900
And the data we're seeing is
that apps that are localized,

00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:10.260
that have localized listings,
are earning 6x more than those

00:14:10.260 --> 00:14:11.520
that aren't.

00:14:11.520 --> 00:14:13.480
So it's very actionable.

00:14:13.480 --> 00:14:15.640
Of course, you can't
translate to every country,

00:14:15.640 --> 00:14:16.620
every language.

00:14:16.620 --> 00:14:19.370
But if you are
intentionally in a market,

00:14:19.370 --> 00:14:22.780
you have to speak
their language.

00:14:22.780 --> 00:14:26.150
The other part is
localizing your pricing.

00:14:26.150 --> 00:14:28.550
And this is, again-- it's one
of those simple things that

00:14:28.550 --> 00:14:32.121
the local developers do
that the foreign ones don't.

00:14:32.121 --> 00:14:34.620
And this is one of those things
that end up impacting sales.

00:14:34.620 --> 00:14:35.930
And then you launch in a market.

00:14:35.930 --> 00:14:37.013
You're like, I don't know.

00:14:37.013 --> 00:14:39.060
I can't crack this
market for some reason.

00:14:39.060 --> 00:14:40.435
But it's because
of little things

00:14:40.435 --> 00:14:43.370
like this, where we have
this incredibly convenient

00:14:43.370 --> 00:14:46.355
auto-convert function
that a lot developers go

00:14:46.355 --> 00:14:48.459
in, they set their default
price, auto-convert.

00:14:48.459 --> 00:14:50.750
And then actually, you don't
go through all the prices,

00:14:50.750 --> 00:14:52.720
and make sure they
are just rounded off.

00:14:52.720 --> 00:14:56.450
They are whatever that
$0.99 equivalent is.

00:14:56.450 --> 00:14:59.230
We all know the
$0.99 price in the US

00:14:59.230 --> 00:15:01.710
has been for decades
a price point

00:15:01.710 --> 00:15:04.480
that we know is like, OK, below
which, it's a trivial purchase,

00:15:04.480 --> 00:15:06.188
or it's a significant
purchase-- whatever

00:15:06.188 --> 00:15:07.330
it is you're targeting.

00:15:07.330 --> 00:15:11.420
But there are equivalents of
those prices in each market.

00:15:11.420 --> 00:15:14.520
So again, 101 Yen
is not one of those.

00:15:14.520 --> 00:15:16.067
It's 100 Yen.

00:15:16.067 --> 00:15:17.900
And as you come through
that purchase flow--

00:15:17.900 --> 00:15:20.480
and you've all probably
optimized your flows--

00:15:20.480 --> 00:15:23.880
every little detail impacts
your conversion rate.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:28.340
And what we've seen here is that
apps and SKUs with prices that

00:15:28.340 --> 00:15:33.160
are local precise local pricing
actually convert and have 2x

00:15:33.160 --> 00:15:35.219
the sales of those that aren't.

00:15:35.219 --> 00:15:37.010
So this is, again, a
very actionable thing.

00:15:37.010 --> 00:15:39.210
Just go through your
pricing, and literally

00:15:39.210 --> 00:15:42.045
make sure it's rounded off.

00:15:42.045 --> 00:15:44.670
But in some cases, you actually
have to change it significantly

00:15:44.670 --> 00:15:48.020
because spending patterns
in different markets

00:15:48.020 --> 00:15:49.970
are different, obviously.

00:15:49.970 --> 00:15:52.180
So this is another small thing.

00:15:52.180 --> 00:15:54.790
The other thing is localizing
your business model.

00:15:54.790 --> 00:15:59.500
It is actually important that
based on your category of app

00:15:59.500 --> 00:16:01.290
as well as what market
you're targeting,

00:16:01.290 --> 00:16:03.010
the intersection
of those two things

00:16:03.010 --> 00:16:04.850
might mean you have
a different business

00:16:04.850 --> 00:16:06.920
model in different countries.

00:16:06.920 --> 00:16:09.680
There are countries where ads
is the primary way of market

00:16:09.680 --> 00:16:10.870
monetizing.

00:16:10.870 --> 00:16:13.770
There are others where
in-app is the way to go.

00:16:13.770 --> 00:16:16.980
For some app categories,
it is subscriptions.

00:16:16.980 --> 00:16:19.910
Others obviously are
paid apps or in-app.

00:16:19.910 --> 00:16:21.680
So again-- and this
is one of those

00:16:21.680 --> 00:16:23.710
you have to take care
of at the beginning,

00:16:23.710 --> 00:16:26.945
as you build your app, as
you build your feature set.

00:16:26.945 --> 00:16:28.320
If it's a
subscription, there has

00:16:28.320 --> 00:16:29.925
to be ongoing
value for the user.

00:16:29.925 --> 00:16:32.690
There has to be recurring value.

00:16:32.690 --> 00:16:34.520
If you are doing
an in-app, then you

00:16:34.520 --> 00:16:38.420
have to have some
incremental discrete steps

00:16:38.420 --> 00:16:40.430
that a user can purchase.

00:16:40.430 --> 00:16:43.100
So again, as you
think through, think

00:16:43.100 --> 00:16:47.700
about localizing your
business models as well.

00:16:47.700 --> 00:16:50.230
So I'm going to talk a little
bit more about subscriptions.

00:16:50.230 --> 00:16:52.850
We've been investing in
subscriptions quite a bit.

00:16:52.850 --> 00:16:55.000
We've seen it be very
successful for apps

00:16:55.000 --> 00:16:57.790
in a number of categories.

00:16:57.790 --> 00:17:00.880
And growth, since launch,
has been tremendous.

00:17:00.880 --> 00:17:03.680
And so we've actually been
investing quite a bit in it.

00:17:03.680 --> 00:17:05.849
As of a couple days ago,
we launched a number

00:17:05.849 --> 00:17:07.960
of new features
for subscriptions,

00:17:07.960 --> 00:17:10.150
including seasonal
subscriptions;

00:17:10.150 --> 00:17:13.380
goodwill credits, where
basically, if somebody's really

00:17:13.380 --> 00:17:15.530
not happy, you an give them
an extra month for free

00:17:15.530 --> 00:17:18.589
via an API; and
also an API for you

00:17:18.589 --> 00:17:22.470
to refund or revoke
subscription access.

00:17:22.470 --> 00:17:24.190
The last upgrades/downgrades
are going

00:17:24.190 --> 00:17:26.202
to launch in the next few weeks.

00:17:26.202 --> 00:17:27.660
So what we're trying
to do is build

00:17:27.660 --> 00:17:30.250
a full-fledged
subscriptions platform

00:17:30.250 --> 00:17:33.810
that is accessible via
APIs that offers you-- we

00:17:33.810 --> 00:17:35.310
take care of all the billing.

00:17:35.310 --> 00:17:38.776
We take care of all the
details of auto-renewing.

00:17:38.776 --> 00:17:41.010
And if it is something
that works for your app,

00:17:41.010 --> 00:17:44.500
if you think that you have
recurring value for users

00:17:44.500 --> 00:17:47.321
over time, then it's
something to consider.

00:17:47.321 --> 00:17:48.820
And we have seen
apps that have been

00:17:48.820 --> 00:17:50.520
successful in all
sorts of categories,

00:17:50.520 --> 00:17:54.740
from education to gaming to
the traditional like music

00:17:54.740 --> 00:17:59.060
and Evernote type of
apps use subscriptions

00:17:59.060 --> 00:18:00.560
and be very
successfully monetizing.

00:18:00.560 --> 00:18:02.930
And so again, think
of subscriptions.

00:18:02.930 --> 00:18:08.290
It is a fast-growing
segment for us.

00:18:08.290 --> 00:18:10.600
This was brought
up earlier as well,

00:18:10.600 --> 00:18:12.870
which is this focus on quality.

00:18:12.870 --> 00:18:16.640
And I wanted to reiterate the
point about those multipliers

00:18:16.640 --> 00:18:17.920
are incredible, right?

00:18:17.920 --> 00:18:22.930
I mean, if you are moving one
star up from the three star

00:18:22.930 --> 00:18:24.580
range to the four
star range, you're

00:18:24.580 --> 00:18:27.360
actually multiplying
your sales by four.

00:18:27.360 --> 00:18:31.140
And so as you think
about investing in QA,

00:18:31.140 --> 00:18:35.920
investing in replying to
reviews, investing in building

00:18:35.920 --> 00:18:38.520
the right product,
this stuff matters

00:18:38.520 --> 00:18:41.340
and has a direct
impact on your sales.

00:18:41.340 --> 00:18:43.947
So you're business owners.

00:18:43.947 --> 00:18:45.530
You need to do the
math and figure out

00:18:45.530 --> 00:18:47.250
if it adds up for you or not.

00:18:47.250 --> 00:18:49.050
But this is hopefully
a metric that

00:18:49.050 --> 00:18:51.390
can help you make that decision.

00:18:51.390 --> 00:18:52.614
Is it worth it for you?

00:18:52.614 --> 00:18:54.030
And I think the
point we're trying

00:18:54.030 --> 00:18:56.900
to make is that it
very much is worth it.

00:18:59.820 --> 00:19:02.540
OK, so this is, again,
along the lines of quality,

00:19:02.540 --> 00:19:04.690
but it's about other
form factors, right?

00:19:04.690 --> 00:19:07.560
And then Android, over
the last of couple months,

00:19:07.560 --> 00:19:09.870
we've launched a
number of new form

00:19:09.870 --> 00:19:11.960
factors, a number
of new ecosystems.

00:19:11.960 --> 00:19:14.550
And the point here
is that if you're

00:19:14.550 --> 00:19:16.690
going to distribute in a
particular form factor,

00:19:16.690 --> 00:19:21.569
whether it's atuo or wear or
tablets or TV, you have to,

00:19:21.569 --> 00:19:22.860
again, be intentional about it.

00:19:22.860 --> 00:19:24.735
You have to actually
build an experience that

00:19:24.735 --> 00:19:26.920
fits that form factor.

00:19:26.920 --> 00:19:29.440
As part of that, we're
seeing that apps that are

00:19:29.440 --> 00:19:32.210
tablet-optimized are actually
monetizing 10 times better than

00:19:32.210 --> 00:19:33.900
those that aren't.

00:19:33.900 --> 00:19:35.550
This stuff, again, matters.

00:19:35.550 --> 00:19:37.560
And you're business owners.

00:19:37.560 --> 00:19:40.120
You're looking to spend
your resources wisely.

00:19:40.120 --> 00:19:42.200
So again, if you're
going to spin off a team

00:19:42.200 --> 00:19:45.932
to build a
tablet-optimized app, this

00:19:45.932 --> 00:19:47.390
is the multiplier
you need to think

00:19:47.390 --> 00:19:48.830
of as you look at
your increasing

00:19:48.830 --> 00:19:54.100
costs versus the potential
increase in reward and sales.

00:19:54.100 --> 00:19:57.210
And I think as these new
ecosystems proliferate

00:19:57.210 --> 00:20:02.320
and as new form factors emerge,
be intentional about it.

00:20:02.320 --> 00:20:05.690
And that will help with your
sales, as you can see here.

00:20:08.470 --> 00:20:13.740
OK, so in closing
and in summary,

00:20:13.740 --> 00:20:15.950
three points to
really take away.

00:20:15.950 --> 00:20:18.970
One is think beyond
your familiar markets.

00:20:18.970 --> 00:20:21.650
Really just do that.

00:20:21.650 --> 00:20:22.990
I know many of you do.

00:20:22.990 --> 00:20:24.490
But there is this
mental shift that

00:20:24.490 --> 00:20:27.490
used to happen in physical
world corporations

00:20:27.490 --> 00:20:28.960
where they go global.

00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:30.730
And I think now,
it happens so fast

00:20:30.730 --> 00:20:34.250
and it's so seamless that
a lot of app developers

00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:36.930
don't actually think
about it and actually

00:20:36.930 --> 00:20:38.820
shift their behavior
accordingly.

00:20:38.820 --> 00:20:41.720
So whether it is localizing
your listings, localizing

00:20:41.720 --> 00:20:47.090
your pricing, et cetera, be
intentional about these things.

00:20:47.090 --> 00:20:49.610
And that's the second
point I just covered.

00:20:49.610 --> 00:20:53.950
And finally, focus on quality
and other form factors.

00:20:53.950 --> 00:20:56.450
Make sure that if
you are actually

00:20:56.450 --> 00:20:58.110
going to submit your
app for tablets,

00:20:58.110 --> 00:21:00.000
make sure it is a
great experience.

00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:02.880
Make sure you build
something tailored for it.

00:21:02.880 --> 00:21:06.930
And users will react well, and
users will increase their spend

00:21:06.930 --> 00:21:09.340
in your app because of that.

00:21:09.340 --> 00:21:11.160
That's all I have for you.

00:21:11.160 --> 00:21:13.220
Thank you very much.

